your little love lives?

14:38.048 --> 14:39.088
Cute.

14:39.089 --> 14:41.090
What do you want?
The judge just accepted

14:41.091 --> 14:42.962
father Andrew's
"not guilty" plea,

14:42.963 --> 14:45.135
so Bonnie wants us
to take a field trip.

14:46.386 --> 14:50.179
Annalise:
Your client has admitted
that they've committed a crime.

14:50.180 --> 14:54.473
How is it possible to argue
a "not guilty" defense?

14:54.474 --> 14:56.066
Why is that
not considered perjury?

14:57.187 --> 14:58.187
Ms. Liebowitz.

14:58.188 --> 14:59.438
Liebowitz:
Two reasons...

14:59.439 --> 15:01.520
One, it's not sworn testimony,

15:01.521 --> 15:04.073
and two, entering a
"not guilty" plea doesn't
mean "i didn't do it,"

15:04.074 --> 15:05.025
it just means that the state

15:05.026 --> 15:06.986
has to prove
every element of the crime

15:06.987 --> 15:08.197
beyond a reasonable doubt.

15:08.198 --> 15:09.698
And that heavy burden

15:09.699 --> 15:11.991
is a defense attorney's
best weapon,

15:11.992 --> 15:14.533
and you got to milk it
for all it's worth.

15:14.534 --> 15:16.996
Joe: About 10:00,
i come through

15:16.997 --> 15:20.039
to light a candle for my wife,
who passed last year.

15:20.040 --> 15:23.963
I come around this pew here,
and i see father Bernard

15:23.964 --> 15:26.005
layin' there
with his head cracked open.

15:26.006 --> 15:28.177
You never seen so much blood.

15:28.178 --> 15:29.678
The wall was sprayed with it.

15:29.679 --> 15:31.890
His Bible,
sittin' on the floor beside him,

15:31.891 --> 15:33.812
was practically floatin' in it.

15:33.813 --> 15:35.314
Want to rack up a couple sins,

15:35.315 --> 15:36.895
give the good lord
a little show?

15:36.896 --> 15:40.059
Then i saw the thurible laying
next to him on the ground.

15:40.060 --> 15:41.060
"Thurible"?

15:41.731 --> 15:43.152
The murder weapon.

15:43.153 --> 15:46.775
Joe: Usually holds the incense,
but that's what did him in.

15:46.776 --> 15:48.527
According to
what you told police,

15:48.528 --> 15:51.160
father Andrew was the first
person you suspected?

15:51.161 --> 15:53.572
I heard them fighting
earlier that week.

15:53.573 --> 15:56.205
Father Andrew hoped
to take over as head pastor

15:56.206 --> 15:58.077
once father Bernard retired,

15:58.078 --> 16:01.290
but father Bernard
wasn't seeing it go that way.

16:01.291 --> 16:03.922
Annalise:
And what about your own ethics?

16:03.923 --> 16:06.085
You know for a fact
that your client is guilty.

16:06.086 --> 16:07.546
They've told you as much.

16:07.547 --> 16:11.220
And yet you have to stand
in front of that jury every day

16:11.221 --> 16:13.852
and lie to their faces.

16:13.853 --> 16:17.146
Is it fair to assume that you
and father Andrew are close?

16:17.147 --> 16:19.688
Um, well, I'm close
with all of the priests.

16:19.689 --> 16:21.650
Yes, that's my job,
to allow the priests

16:21.651 --> 16:24.153
to focus on their divine office
and their teaching.

16:24.154 --> 16:25.694
Is there anything that you know

16:25.695 --> 16:27.526
that could help
in father Andrew's defense?

16:27.527 --> 16:30.819
I assume that's something
you're interested in.

16:30.820 --> 16:32.321
Why would i want to do that?

16:32.322 --> 16:34.743
Because just the sight of you
in the courtroom

16:34.744 --> 16:37.746
gave him second thoughts about
spending 30 years behind bars.

16:37.747 --> 16:39.788
I know what you're implying,

16:39.789 --> 16:42.081
but father Andrew
is a pious man.

16:42.082 --> 16:43.082
A man you love.

16:44.334 --> 16:48.797
Well, it's not like we're
in a position to act on that.

16:48.798 --> 16:49.968
We've made our choices.

16:49.969 --> 16:51.221
Excuse me.

16:52.762 --> 16:54.343
You lie to yourself.

16:54.344 --> 16:55.844
That's how you do it.

16:55.845 --> 16:57.976
You lie.

16:57.977 --> 16:59.518
And you tell yourself

16:59.519 --> 17:01.900
that that client
who you know did it did not.

17:01.901 --> 17:06.405
Because dwelling in that truth
won't let you do your job.

17:06.406 --> 17:08.197
Michaela:
A student killed himself?

17:08.198 --> 17:11.029
Brian kamens. He hanged himself
in his grandma's garage.

17:11.030 --> 17:13.412
Let me guess... he was
an altar boy getting the...

17:13.413 --> 17:15.154
Holy treatment
from some of the priests here?

17:15.155 --> 17:16.745
Not all priests are pedophiles.

17:16.746 --> 17:17.746
Since when?

17:17.747 --> 17:18.827
Truth.

17:18.828 --> 17:20.999
Zach:
Brian and father Andrew

17:21.000 --> 17:23.212
spent a lot of time
in the dark room together...

17:23.213 --> 17:25.505
Doing... Photography.

17:28.628 --> 17:31.090
Then he killed himself.

17:31.091 --> 17:32.091
That tell you enough?

17:32.092 --> 17:33.932
Were you molesting Brian kamens?

17:33.933 --> 17:35.224
Of course not.

17:35.225 --> 17:37.636
Father Bernard confronted you
about what you did to Brian,

17:37.637 --> 17:39.518
and he was
gonna report you.
I did not
touch that boy.

17:39.519 --> 17:40.979
You had to silence
father Bernard

17:40.980 --> 17:42.481
because he knew
your dirty little secret.

17:42.482 --> 17:43.562
How dare you?

17:43.563 --> 17:46.486
I humiliated myself in court
for you, father.

17:48.148 --> 17:50.490
You do not get to lie to me.

17:52.112 --> 17:53.072
[ Sighs ]

17:53.073 --> 17:55.694
Brian and i spent
considerable time together.

17:55.695 --> 17:57.246
The dark room had become

17:57.247 --> 18:01.160
a place where he felt safe
enough to tell me, his friend,

18:01.161 --> 18:02.871
what was troubling him...

18:02.872 --> 18:05.754
That he was
being abused by someone.

18:05.755 --> 18:07.337
And shortly after his death...

18:09.169 --> 18:13.051
i came to learn that person
was father Bernard.

18:13.052 --> 18:14.514
That's why i killed him.

18:16.266 --> 18:18.308
And I'd do it again.

18:27.066 --> 18:28.937
I was devastated knowing
that Brian had been abused,

18:28.938 --> 18:32.030
that whoever did it
had driven him to kill himself.

18:32.031 --> 18:34.493
I wanted to find that monster.

18:34.494 --> 18:36.405
I prayed on it.

18:36.406 --> 18:40.160
And then, one night,
god brought him to me.

18:43.503 --> 18:46.205
Father Bernard: Forgive me,
father, for i have sinned.

18:46.206 --> 18:48.207
He never mentioned Brian
by name.

18:48.208 --> 18:51.460
I tried to stop myself...
I did...

18:51.461 --> 18:54.052
Praying to god for his mercy,

18:54.053 --> 18:58.136
but each time i went near him...

18:58.137 --> 18:59.928
I couldn't stop myself.

18:59.929 --> 19:03.061
Father Andrew:
I finally had my answer.

19:03.062 --> 19:05.564
Give thanks to the lord,
for he is good.

19:05.565 --> 19:08.067
For his mercy endures forever.

19:10.029 --> 19:12.150
Father Andrew: I thought about
breaking the sacrament,

19:12.151 --> 19:13.862
reporting what he'd told me,

19:13.863 --> 19:16.866
but i knew
they'd just transfer him...

19:18.578 --> 19:20.580
that he'd find another Brian.

19:36.636 --> 19:39.388
I waited for the guilt to come,

19:39.389 --> 19:42.931
and when it didn't,
i was confused.

19:42.932 --> 19:46.265
Part of me wondered
if i hadn't done his will...

19:46.266 --> 19:49.017
For Brian.

19:49.018 --> 19:52.652
I know what i did was wrong.

19:54.113 --> 19:57.025
I just don't feel it was wrong.

19:57.026 --> 19:59.488
Michaela: So we plead
manslaughter instead of murder?

19:59.489 --> 20:01.820
We can't. Father Andrew
feels that it's a sin

20:01.821 --> 20:04.373
to testify to what
father Bernard said in
the confessional booth,

20:04.374 --> 20:07.085
and evidentiary law
agrees with him.

20:07.086 --> 20:08.457
So, without that piece
of information,

20:08.458 --> 20:10.168
we can't convince a jury
this was manslaughter.

20:10.169 --> 20:11.671
What about
the "Thorn birds" angle?

20:13.333 --> 20:14.713
The miniseries?

20:14.714 --> 20:16.335
You know, Richard Chamberlain,
he's a priest,

20:16.336 --> 20:18.176
gets down with his lady friend?
It's pretty good.

20:18.177 --> 20:19.508
Both Agnes and father Andrew

20:19.509 --> 20:21.550
claim that their relationship
was platonic.

20:21.551 --> 20:23.262
Well, yeah. That's what i
used to tell my parents

20:23.263 --> 20:24.603
about me and our neighbor, Cole.

20:24.604 --> 20:26.104
It's not an angle
we can work right now.

20:26.105 --> 20:27.226
Keep thinking.

20:28.978 --> 20:32.060
Was i right, or was i right?

20:32.061 --> 20:34.152
[ Irish accent ] It all comes
back to the diddlin' priests.

20:34.153 --> 20:35.114
So, you're happy

20:35.115 --> 20:37.356
a boy was sexually abused
and then killed himself?

20:37.357 --> 20:39.989
No, I'm happy because
I'm awesome sauce.

20:52.372 --> 20:54.212
Now what?

20:54.213 --> 20:56.675
The detective's notes
on the murder book.

20:56.676 --> 20:58.877
He has Rebecca
at Griffin's fraternity

20:58.878 --> 21:00.589
a little after midnight, right?

21:00.590 --> 21:01.590
Mm-hmm.

21:02.642 --> 21:04.093
[ Both breathing heavily ]

21:13.022 --> 21:14.102
[ Knock on door ]

21:14.103 --> 21:15.193
[ Door opens ]

21:15.194 --> 21:16.655
Get the hell out of here!

21:16.656 --> 21:18.067
Lila: Griffin?

21:20.069 --> 21:21.530
[ Voice breaking ]
I got your text.

21:21.531 --> 21:22.531
Lila.

21:23.823 --> 21:25.575
You still think he's worth it?

21:26.326 --> 21:29.037
You stupid slut!

21:29.038 --> 21:30.329
[ All shouting ]

21:30.330 --> 21:31.530
How could you
do this?!
Get off!

21:36.546 --> 21:39.508
I never want to see
either of you again!

21:39.509 --> 21:40.629
[ Crying ]

21:40.630 --> 21:43.592
Screaming, scratching me.

21:43.593 --> 21:45.884
That's why my DNA
is under her nails.

21:45.885 --> 21:48.306
And that's when i see Rebecca...

21:48.307 --> 21:49.599
Smiling.

21:52.772 --> 21:53.982
Wes:
The police report

21:53.983 --> 21:55.814
says people saw Lila
leave the frat house

21:55.815 --> 21:57.566
around 12:30 A.M.

21:57.567 --> 21:59.277
Then some guy
from the basketball team

21:59.278 --> 22:01.199
saw someone fitting
Rebecca's description

22:01.200 --> 22:02.901
between 1:00 and 2:00 A.M.

22:02.902 --> 22:04.032
An eyewitness?

22:04.033 --> 22:05.904
Why didn't we ever hear that?

22:05.905 --> 22:07.866
He identified
a different girl's photo.

22:07.867 --> 22:09.247
So, it wasn't Rebecca.

22:09.248 --> 22:10.909
Or he just picked
the wrong photo.

22:10.910 --> 22:12.541
In his statement,

22:12.542 --> 22:15.834
the basketball player said
he saw Rebecca on spruce road.

22:15.835 --> 22:18.547
That's near Lila's sorority,

22:18.548 --> 22:21.009
which means Rebecca didn't
go home after the fight

22:21.010 --> 22:22.591
like she said
in her first statement,

22:22.592 --> 22:24.222
she went to the sorority house,

22:24.223 --> 22:26.675
which matches what she said
in her confession tape.

22:26.676 --> 22:28.638
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

22:31.100 --> 22:34.644
No, answer it, so she
doesn't get suspicious.

22:39.318 --> 22:40.529
Hey.

22:40.530 --> 22:43.191
Hey. Uh, look, I'm gonna
be home late tonight.

22:43.192 --> 22:45.984
Bruce got boned by a couple of
his bartenders, and he's short,

22:45.985 --> 22:47.696
so i just got here
to pick up a shift.

22:47.697 --> 22:50.038
At the bar? Really?

22:50.039 --> 22:51.249
You sure you want
to go back there?

22:51.250 --> 22:54.122
Yeah. It's one night.
I could use the cash.

22:54.123 --> 22:56.204
You should come by
after work. Free beer.

22:56.205 --> 22:57.996
I don't know, um...

22:57.997 --> 22:59.377
I think we're gonna be stuck

22:59.378 --> 23:00.840
working on this case
for a while.

23:01.921 --> 23:04.053
Yeah. Okay.

23:07.136 --> 23:08.306
I love you.

23:08.307 --> 23:10.349
Love you too.

23:16.936 --> 23:19.439
[ Sighs ]

23:24.323 --> 23:25.944
Father Andrew:
I cannot betray my vows.

23:25.945 --> 23:26.985
Of course you can.

23:26.986 --> 23:29.117
You just get up on that stand,
and you testify

23:29.118 --> 23:31.369
that you killed a pedophile that
drove a boy to kill himself.

23:31.370 --> 23:33.161
The d.A. Will knock it down
to voluntary manslaughter.

23:33.162 --> 23:34.993
You might even get to walk.

23:34.994 --> 23:36.705
The sacramental seal
is inviolable.

23:36.706 --> 23:37.796
I will not betray it.

23:37.797 --> 23:39.337
You won't betray an institution

23:39.338 --> 23:41.750
that created the environment
for the abuse to occur?

23:41.751 --> 23:44.172
Father Bernard's sin
is his alone.

23:44.173 --> 23:46.304
Why should it influence
my commitment to the lord?

23:46.305 --> 23:48.717
You killed someone.
What would the lord
think about that?

23:48.718 --> 23:50.388
I did something terrible, yes,

23:50.389 --> 23:52.551
but that doesn't mean that i
can continue down that road.

23:52.552 --> 23:54.052
Even if it means
staying out prison,

23:54.053 --> 23:55.353
getting to be
with the woman you love?

23:55.354 --> 23:57.937
Agnes and i
never acted on our feelings!

23:59.318 --> 24:01.190
[ Breathing heavily ]

24:06.365 --> 24:07.196
[ Sighs ]

24:07.197 --> 24:09.868
Life is messy, father.

24:09.869 --> 24:13.782
We all have to make compromises
in order to be happy.

24:13.783 --> 24:15.784
That's a terribly cynical
way to live.

24:15.785 --> 24:18.837
Well, i have
my reasons.
Really?

24:18.838 --> 24:19.838
What are they?

24:19.839 --> 24:21.130
[ Groans ]

24:25.384 --> 24:26.846
Come.

24:28.548 --> 24:31.510
Cast your burden on the lord,
and he will sustain you.

24:31.511 --> 24:33.892
I'm your lawyer.
Exactly.

24:33.893 --> 24:37.096
My job requires the same level
of confidentiality as yours.

24:44.814 --> 24:46.314
No god should forgive me

24:46.315 --> 24:48.367
for all the bad things
that I've done.

24:49.158 --> 24:51.369
I'm wasting both of our time.

24:51.370 --> 24:53.742
Don't worry, i still plan
to win your case,

24:53.743 --> 24:55.745
even if you refuse to help.

24:57.416 --> 24:59.377
Asher: [ Ditzy voice ]
I'm so confused.

24:59.378 --> 25:02.671
Does the book go here?

25:02.672 --> 25:04.042
Or maybe i should put it...

25:04.043 --> 25:05.214
Here.

25:06.796 --> 25:09.387
[ Normal voice ] This is exactly
the book i was looking for.

25:09.388 --> 25:10.890
My office, frank.

25:18.638 --> 25:20.019
[ Sighs ]

25:27.526 --> 25:30.199
Is your connection at
the central jail still good?

25:31.280 --> 25:33.151
Maybe.
What's up?

25:33.152 --> 25:34.362
Do you have the connection
or not?

25:34.363 --> 25:36.364
Is this about Nate?

25:36.365 --> 25:37.577
Something happen to him?

25:38.998 --> 25:40.249
Not yet.

26:00.600 --> 26:02.771
How many sexual partners
have you had in the last year?

26:02.772 --> 26:03.943
An estimate's fine.

26:05.645 --> 26:07.105
20?

26:07.106 --> 26:08.526
So, less than two a month?

26:08.527 --> 26:09.898
[ Chuckles ]

26:09.899 --> 26:12.491
Okay, probably, uh,
probably more like 30.

26:13.863 --> 26:15.243
40, i...

26:15.244 --> 26:17.115
How often do you use a condom?

26:17.116 --> 26:18.998
Always.

26:20.159 --> 26:22.160
Well, okay, you know, i mean,

26:22.161 --> 26:24.002
definitely when I'm on...

26:24.003 --> 26:25.253
The bottom bunk,

26:25.254 --> 26:27.375
and I'd say...

26:27.376 --> 26:29.207
80% on top.

26:29.208 --> 26:32.470
You know, some guys
ask me not to, and i...

26:32.471 --> 26:34.172
I heard it's harder
to contract if you're...

26:34.173 --> 26:35.213
On the top bunk?
Yeah.

26:35.214 --> 26:36.805
That's wrong.

26:36.806 --> 26:39.768
You can contract HIV
giving and receiving.

26:39.769 --> 26:42.020
Has your current partner
or any former partners

26:42.021 --> 26:44.643
ever been diagnosed
or treated for an std?

26:44.644 --> 26:45.684
[ Sighs ]

26:45.685 --> 26:47.025
Connor:
You're right...

26:47.026 --> 26:48.647
This is so romantic.

26:48.648 --> 26:50.318
It will be in 20 minutes

26:50.319 --> 26:52.360
when you get your results
and we go home to celebrate.

26:52.361 --> 26:53.862
You know, i, um...

26:53.863 --> 26:55.153
I actually have to go to class.

26:55.154 --> 26:57.115
Esther: Oliver?
Yeah.

26:57.116 --> 26:58.616
[ Chuckles ]
Wish me luck.

26:58.617 --> 26:59.868
Uh, excuse me, could...

26:59.869 --> 27:01.449
Could you give me
my results over the phone?

27:01.450 --> 27:03.162
Yep.

27:04.333 --> 27:05.705
I'll call you when i hear.

27:14.303 --> 27:15.964
Bonnie: Annalise?

27:15.965 --> 27:16.926
What?

27:16.927 --> 27:18.217
It's Nate.

27:19.719 --> 27:23.101
He was attacked
last night in jail.

27:23.102 --> 27:26.686
Some guys beat him up pretty
bad, but he's going to be okay.

27:33.272 --> 27:34.363
Oh...

27:35.735 --> 27:37.736
That's what you and frank...

27:37.737 --> 27:40.618
How else were we
gonna get him out of jail?

27:40.619 --> 27:42.620
Annalise...

27:42.621 --> 27:45.083
Judge Redding already denied

27:45.084 --> 27:47.205
the request
for a new bail hearing.

27:47.206 --> 27:51.170
She ordered him to be placed
in solitary instead.

27:58.888 --> 28:00.760
[ Sighs ]

28:09.518 --> 28:11.149
Where's Mr. millstone?

28:11.150 --> 28:14.312
Um, in class, i think.

28:14.313 --> 28:16.233
Call and tell him that
we're gonna need his help.

28:20.159 --> 28:21.489
I don't like this.

28:21.490 --> 28:23.201
We got orders.

28:23.202 --> 28:25.994
He's the only one who's
anonymous in all of this.

28:25.995 --> 28:27.996
We could be
compromising his future.

28:27.997 --> 28:30.588
Since when do you care so much
about doucheface's future?

28:30.589 --> 28:32.751
I heard my mad skills
were desired.

28:32.752 --> 28:34.632
Yeah. We need help
on father Andrew's case.
Sweet.

28:34.633 --> 28:37.005
Anything that makes
me look better to the
big boss man upstairs.

28:37.006 --> 28:38.636
Uh, or woman.

28:38.637 --> 28:40.508
See that woman
standing over there?

28:40.509 --> 28:41.760
That's judge Redding.

28:41.761 --> 28:43.641
I am denying
the request for bail.

28:43.642 --> 28:45.143
Walk over, say hello.

28:45.144 --> 28:47.015
Drop the old millstone name
to break the ice.

28:47.016 --> 28:48.016
What's the catch?

28:48.017 --> 28:49.517
You want to seize the moment

28:49.518 --> 28:51.729
or stand here and talk about it
till it's gone?

28:51.730 --> 28:53.311
Hurry up.

28:53.312 --> 28:55.353
Secret agent man...

28:55.354 --> 28:58.696
All mission, no details.
That's how i like to roll.

28:58.697 --> 29:00.199
B-r-b.

29:01.490 --> 29:03.071
Asher:
Judge Redding.

29:03.072 --> 29:05.453
Asher millstone,
son to judge William millstone.
[ Gasps ]

29:05.454 --> 29:06.624
Oh, my goodness!
How's your dad?

29:06.625 --> 29:08.166
Oh, he's good.
He's wonderful.
Yeah?

29:08.167 --> 29:10.248
He's just catching up
on the old game.
What are you up to?

29:10.249 --> 29:12.791
I'm going to school, middleton,
studying law.

29:12.792 --> 29:14.172
Annalise:
So, you don't love him?

29:14.173 --> 29:15.834
Like i told you before,

29:15.835 --> 29:17.175
not in the way
that you're suggesting.

29:17.176 --> 29:18.797
Which way, then, like a brother?

29:18.798 --> 29:21.089
Annalise:
So long as you hide it,

29:21.090 --> 29:23.431
there's no way
that you can help me defend him.

29:23.432 --> 29:24.762
I don't understand.

29:24.763 --> 29:26.514
How can i help him?
I'm not involved in any of this.

29:26.515 --> 29:27.596
